1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15-10 and a new section to
2 chapter 26.1-02 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the acceptance of health care
3 sharing ministries by an institution of higher education and health care sharing ministries'
4 exemptions from insurance laws and regulations.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15-10 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Institutions of higher education - Acceptance of health care sharing ministries as
9 health care coverage.
10 A student's active participation in a health care sharing ministry, as that term is defined
11 under section 2 of this Act, satisfies any requirement that a student enrolled in an institution o f
12 higher education maintain health care coverage.
13 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 26.1-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Health care sharing ministry.
16 1. A health care sharing ministry may not be considered to be engaging in the business
17 of insurance and is exempt from regulations applicable to insurance entities.
18 2. As used in this section, "health care sharing ministry" means a nonprofit organization
19 that:
20 a. Is recognized as tax exempt under section 501(c)(3) of the United States Internal
21 Revenue Code [26 U.S.C. 501(c)(3)];
22 b. Limits its participants to members who share a common set of ethical or religious
23 beliefs;
