1 c. Acts as a facilitator among participants who have financial or medical needs to
2 assist participants with financial or medical needs according to criteria
3 established by the health care sharing ministry;
4 d. With no assumption of risk or promise to pay, provides for the financial or medical
5 needs of a participant through contributions from other participants, which were
6 contributed by participants with no assumption of risk or promise to pay;
7 e. Monthly provides to participants the total dollar amount of qualified needs shared
8 during the previous month according to criteria established by the health care
9 sharing ministry;
10 f. Annually conducts an audit performed by an independent certified public
11 accounting firm according to generally accepted accounting principles and
12 publishes the audit on the health care sharing ministry's website or provides a
13 copy upon request; and
14 g. Provides a written disclaimer on or accompanying all applications and guideline
15 materials distributed by or on behalf of the organization which explains:
16 (1) The organization facilitating the sharing of medical expenses is not an
17 insurance company and its guidelines and plan of operation are not an
18 insurance policy;
19 (2) Whether anyone chooses to assist the participant with medical bills is
20 voluntary;
21 (3) Participation in the organization or a subscription to its documents is not
22 insurance; and
23 (4) Regardless of whether the participant receives payments or the organization
24 continues to operate, the participant is responsible for the payment of the
25 participant's medical bills.
